Class JavaTypeMapEntries

  oracle.jbo.common.JboTypeMapEntries

Direct Known Subclasses:
JavaTypeMapEntries
public class JavaTypeMapEntries
extends JboTypeMapEntries

Populates TypeMap Entries for BC4J Designtime and Runtime to map a Database column type to a java-class type and also to jdbc-sqltype and id. The entries should be: COLUMN_TYPE - column type in the database JAVA_CLASS_NAME - Java class which should store in-memory data from the given column-type JDBC_SQL_TYPE - Name of the jdbc sql type id that the subsequent integer-entry represents. JDBC_SQL_TYPE_ID - Integer value from java.sql.Types or a corresponding Types list in jdbc. DISPLAY_LENGTH - Default size for various String/Character types.

Since:
JDeveloper 3.2
